                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#56vb">f. 56vb</locus>
                           <desc>: Ownership note.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#56vb">56vb</locus>: በስመ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ዛቲ፡
                              መጽሐፍ፡ ዘአባእኮ፡ ዘደብረ፡ </quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en">
                              <locus target="#56vb">56vb</locus>: In the name of the Father, the Son
                              and the Holy Spirit. This book is of Dabra ʾAbaʾǝko. </quote>
                           <note> The note is written in a crude hand. The name of the church of
                              ʾAbaǝʾko is attested in other Mss. of Mǝdra Ruba, e.g., MR-012,
                              MR-012. It seems to be one of several churches in the area which
                              disappeared, but whose tabots and books were brought to the church of
                              Mǝdra Ruba. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#81rb">f. 81rb</locus>
                           <desc>: Protective prayer for healing wounds.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez">
                              <locus target="#81rb">81rb</locus>: ጸሎተ፡ ቍስል፡ ሰተናዊ፡ ቀተናዊ፡ ወግድ፡
                              አምላክ፡... </quote>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> </note>
                        </item>
